name=&quot;XE_change_control_manager_(role)__description_of&quot;>&lt;/a>&lt;a id=&quot;Description&quot; name=&quot;Description&quot;>&lt;/a></mainDescription>
  <skills>&lt;a id=&quot;Skills&quot; name=&quot;Skills&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The person playing the &lt;a class=&quot;PresentationName&quot; guid=&quot;{C1D3C2C0-15A0-49AD-9788-8C163E53CB96}&quot;>Change Control&#xD;
    Manager&lt;/a> should understand configuration management principles.&amp;nbsp; They should be skilled in estimating cost and&#xD;
    schedule impacts of change requests. They should be able to communicate effectively in order to negotiate scope changes&#xD;
    and in order to determine how each change request should be handled and by whom.&#xD;
&lt;/p></skills>
  <assignmentApproaches>&lt;a id=&quot;RoleAssignmentApproaches&quot; name=&quot;RoleAssignmentApproaches&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This role is often shared by a Configuration (or Change) Control Board (CCB) and consists of representatives from all&#xD;
    interested parties, including customers, developers, and users. In a small project, a single team member, such as the&#xD;
    project manager or software architect, may play this role.&#xD;
&lt;/p></assignmentApproaches>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:RoleDescription>
